The paper presents a novel siamese network for visual tracking, which is a popular topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The network also incorporates classification, regression, and localization branches, which are common techniques in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of the standard SGD algorithm with back-propagation, which is a common optimization technique in deep learning (cs.LG). The network is designed for tracking moving objects, which is a common problem in robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the network on several benchmark datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM).
